8G3gD8OJdnmPz1o9bg2yCw
This is the best Vietnamese food I've had in the Phoenix area. They have a limited menu but most of the dishes are done well. I sampled banh xeo, pho, bun bo hue, banh cuon, and bun thit nuong. I would order any of those again here. The service is a bit slow for Vietnamese food, but the prices are fair.  To be more authentic, I would suggest they add banana blossom to their BBH and offer ngo gai (culantro) to their pho herbs. I would come much more often if I lived close by. The food is much better than any of the Viet places in Central Phoenix.

